Basic Information: Full Name: Alex Carter. Current/Desired Title: Entry-Level Front-End Developer. Location: Portland, OR, United States (127 Maple Ridge Lane, Apt 3B, Portland, OR 97205). Contact Information: Email: alex.carter.dev@example.com. Phone: (503) 555-0198. LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/alexcarter-dev. GitHub: github.com/alexcarter-dev. Website: www.alexcarter.dev. Work Authorization: Authorized to work in the U.S. without sponsorship. Open to hybrid and remote positions.

Professional Summary: Alex Carter is an enthusiastic and detail-oriented entry-level front-end developer with approximately 14 months of professional experience, primarily focused on React and React Native in a hybrid work environment at Northwind Digital Labs. Recently promoted from Junior Developer due to performance, Alex is actively growing skills in modern Angular (versions 16 and 17) through self-driven projects and intends to transition into Angular 2+ roles. Strengths include component-based UI development, thorough documentation, eagerness to learn via code review, and a strong grasp of state management, responsive design, and accessibility best practices. Proficient in JavaScript, TypeScript (growing), and a range of modern FE tools, Alex has a history of cross-platform UI work and is recognized for clear communication and ownership of deliverables.

Work History:
1. Front-End Developer (Promoted from Junior)
   - Company: Northwind Digital Labs
   - Location: Portland, OR (Hybrid)
   - Dates: June 2023 – Present (14 months total); promoted within 12 months
   - Responsibilities and Achievements:
     - Built and maintained reusable component libraries for React-based internal design systems, contributing over 20 production-quality UI components (buttons, dialogs, layouts). Authored detailed documentation, usage examples, and accessibility notes in Storybook.
     - Led accessibility improvements, raising Lighthouse scores from 72 to 93 through semantic HTML, ARIA, key bindings, and color adjustments.
     - Implemented shared UI logic and platform-specific designs across web (React) and mobile (React Native) apps.
     - Managed API state using Redux Toolkit and React Query, including design of optimistic UI flows and robust error handling.
     - Consistently wrote and maintained unit/integration tests (Jest, React Testing Library), maintaining 85–95% coverage and debugging asynchronous UI states.
     - Assisted in maintenance and gradual refactoring of a legacy AngularJS (1.x) internal tool; performed bug fixes and minor upgrades.
     - Fully participated in Agile ceremonies (standups, planning, retros, ticket creation), proactively requested code reviews, and fostered best practices in FE architecture and CSS design token usage.
     - Mentored newer interns and was recognized for clear documentation, communication, and initiative.

Education:
- B.S. in Computer & Information Science, University of Oregon, Eugene, OR, 2018-2022; GPA: 3.5/4.0. Focused on Web Development, Human-Computer Interaction. Relevant coursework: Web App Development (JavaScript, AngularJS, REST), UI/UX Design, Mobile App Development (intro React Native), Software Engineering (Agile, Git, docs), Data Structures & Algorithms (Java). Notable projects include a responsive course planner (vanilla JS, CSS Grid) and HCI usability study (personas, reports).

Certifications, Courses, and Training:
- Completed several Angular 14–17 courses (Udemy and official Angular documentation), focusing on components, DI, routing, RxJS. No formal certifications listed. Maintains personal Angular notes and actively follows Angular community/training content (e.g., NG Conf, Angular Blog).

Skills:
Technical Skills (Top Skills with Approximate Levels):
- JavaScript (ES6+): Advanced (core language for all roles/projects, substantial experience)
- React: Advanced (core in professional work, library development, cross-platform UI)
- React Native: Intermediate-Advanced (14 months of direct experience, shipped mobile UI)
- TypeScript: Intermediate (growing proficiency, applied in personal/professional projects)
- Angular (2+, 16–17): Intermediate-Basic (actively learning, robust personal projects, not yet in production)
- Redux Toolkit, React Query, NgRx, RxJS: Intermediate (prominently used in projects and main role)
- CSS3, SASS/SCSS, Styled Components, CSS Modules, Tailwind: Advanced (multiple styling frameworks, strong in both pro and personal work)
- HTML5, ARIA/Accessibility: Advanced (lead accessibility improvements, routine semantic markup)
- Testing: Jest, React Testing Library, Cypress: Intermediate (routine professional testing with high test coverage)
- Git & GitHub, Webpack, Vite, ESLint, Prettier: Intermediate-Advanced (daily tooling)
- Node.js (tooling & basic APIs): Basic-Intermediate
- REST APIs: Intermediate (integrations and state/APIs in all major roles/projects)
- Express, MongoDB (basic/intro)

Non-Technical Skills:
- Clear written and verbal communication (PRs, code reviews)
- Detail-oriented documentation
- Agile participation
- Team collaboration
- Mentoring/intern onboarding
- Initiative and feedback seeking

Projects:
- TaskFlow Pro (Kanban Productivity App): Personal Angular 17 project focusing on best practices, global state with NgRx, RxJS streams, feature modules, Angular Material theming, robust form validations. Documented learning and build notes extensively (github.com/alexcarter-dev/taskflow-pro-angular).
- FitTrack Mobile: Personal React Native app for workout tracking, built with focus on reusable components, navigation, local persistence, and maintainable styles. Code and screenshots available (github.com/alexcarter-dev/fittrack-mobile).
- Campus Event Explorer: Senior capstone, team web app (React, Node.js, MongoDB), front-end led by Alex, with responsive design, event filtering/bookmarking, style guides, team navigation components.
- Student Budget Planner (AngularJS): Campus project managing expenses with AngularJS controllers/services; first exposure to SPA, client-side routing, and API integration.
- Additional: Single-page resume site (HTML, CSS, vanilla JS), responsive photo gallery (CSS Grid/Flexbox), utility JS algorithm/practice snippets.

Awards, Honors, and Recognition: Promoted from Junior Developer within 12 months at Northwind Digital Labs based on code quality, proactive learning, documentation, and mentorship. No distinct external awards stated.

Languages: English (no others explicitly listed).

Extracurriculars and Interests: Regularly attends local tech meetups (Portland JavaScript, Angular/Frontend), recreates UI components for practice (CodeSandbox), follows FE industry blogs (CSS-Tricks, Smashing Magazine, Angular Blog).

Professional Interests: Particularly passionate about accessible, responsive UIs, state management, learning new frameworks, and collaborating in code reviews. Enjoys cross-functional/Agile teams and continuous learning.

Personality Interpretation (Subjective Inference): Based on the resume, Alex exhibits a detail-oriented, proactive communication style and a deep investment in thorough documentation and quality. There is a strong learning mindset, evidenced by regular feedback-seeking, self-driven study outside immediate job demands, and careful tracking of new frameworks and industry trends. The resume reflects both pride in technical achievement and a collaborative approach, with highlights regarding mentorship, code reviews, and team-oriented Agile practices. Alex appears to thrive in environments where best practices, readability, and new technology adoption are valued, and seems well suited to roles requiring both technical depth and cross-team communication.

Overall Profile Summary: Alex Carter is an early-career front-end developer with roughly 14 months of production experience at Northwind Digital Labs, primarily using React and React Native. Promoted in under a year due to technical reliability, code quality, accessibility initiatives, and team mentorship. Alex is increasingly specializing in state management (Redux, React Query, NgRx), component libraries, and UI accessibility, and actively expanding skills into modern Angular through self-driven projects, online coursework, and community engagement. Thrives in collaborative, Agile teams with clear engineering standards, mentorship, and an appetite for continuous learning and refactoring. Particularly equipped for roles on teams transitioning toward modern FE stacks (e.g., migrating old AngularJS to Angular 2+ or React), with a strong appetite for codebase quality, UI architecture, and documentation. Driven by curiosity and a sense of ownership, Alex seeks junior/entry-level positions with growth potential, mentoring, and involvement in UI/UX, accessibility, and state management challenges.

# Professional Summary
Front-end developer with approximately 14 months of professional experience primarily in React and React Native, recently promoted from Junior Developer at Northwind Digital Labs. Strong command of JavaScript and fluency with component-based interface development, state management, responsive UI, and accessibility. Building advanced skills in Angular 16–17 via hands-on projects and formal courses. Renowned for thorough documentation, feedback-seeking behavior, and enthusiastic participation in code review and architectural discussion. Consistently recognized for detail-oriented work, clear communication, and ownership of end-to-end front-end deliverables.

# Work History
## Northwind Digital Labs  
**Front-End Developer (Promoted from Junior)**  
*Portland, OR (Hybrid), Jun 2023 – Present (14 months total)*
- Joined as Junior Front-End Developer (React/React Native), promoted to Front-End Developer within 12 months for high-quality technical contributions and mentorship.
- **Technology Stack:** React (18), React Native, JavaScript (ES2020+), TypeScript (introductory), Redux Toolkit, React Query, Styled Components, SASS, Storybook, Jest, React Testing Library, Git, REST APIs, Webpack, Vite, Node.js (tooling), basic AngularJS.
- **Key Responsibilities and Achievements:**
  - Developed and documented 20+ reusable React components for an internal design system, with Storybook usage guides and accessibility notes.
  - Led accessibility efforts, raising Lighthouse scores from 72 to 93 using semantic HTML, ARIA, keyboard navigation, and color-contrast improvements.
  - Managed state with Redux Toolkit/React Query for a production dashboard, including optimistic UIs and robust error handling.
  - Routinely wrote unit/integration tests with Jest/React Testing Library, maintaining 85–95% coverage for owned components.
  - Assisted with legacy AngularJS tool maintenance and facilitated gradual refactoring efforts.
  - Championed Agile adoption: attended ceremonies, groomed tickets, communicated best FE architecture practices, and mentored interns.
  - Consistently recognized for proactive communication, documentation, and experimental learning (e.g., CSS architecture, design tokens).

# Education
- **B.S. in Computer & Information Science**, University of Oregon, Eugene, OR (2018–2022)
  - GPA: 3.5/4.0
  - Focus: Web Development, Human-Computer Interaction
  - **Relevant Coursework:**
    - Web Application Development (JavaScript, AngularJS, REST APIs)
    - UI/UX Design
    - Mobile App Development (Intro to React Native)
    - Software Engineering (Agile, Git, documentation)
    - Data Structures & Algorithms (Java)
  - **Notable Academic Projects:**
    - *Interactive Course Planner*: Responsive JS/CSS UI for scheduling
    - *HCI Usability Study*: User research and accessibility report for a mock app

# Certifications, Courses, and Training
- Completed several Angular 14–17 courses (Udemy, Angular Docs): Focused on components, services, DI, routing, RxJS
- Maintains personal "Angular Notes" repository documenting common patterns and migration notes
- Follows Angular Blog, NG Conf, and community resources for up-to-date learning

# Technical Skills
## Languages & Core
- JavaScript (ES6+): **Advanced**
- TypeScript: **Intermediate** (growing)
- HTML5/CSS3: **Advanced**

## Front-End Frameworks/Libraries
- React: **Advanced**
- React Native: **Intermediate-Advanced**
- Redux Toolkit, React Query: **Intermediate**
- Angular 16–17: **Intermediate-Basic** (personal projects)
- NgRx, RxJS: **Intermediate**
- AngularJS (1.x): **Basic-Intermediate** (maintenance, lab projects)

## Styling Tools
- CSS Modules, SASS/SCSS: **Advanced**
- Styled Components: **Advanced**
- Tailwind CSS: **Intermediate**
- Flexbox, CSS Grid: **Advanced**

## Tooling & Testing
- Git & GitHub: **Advanced**
- Webpack, Vite: **Intermediate**
- Jest, React Testing Library: **Intermediate**
- Storybook: **Advanced**
- ESLint, Prettier: **Intermediate-Advanced**
- npm, Yarn: **Intermediate**

## Back-End & APIs
- Node.js: **Intermediate** (for tooling/simple APIs)
- Express: **Basic**
- MongoDB: **Basic**
- REST APIs: **Intermediate**
- JSON Server: **Basic**

## Soft/Other Skills
- Clear/team-oriented communication
- Documentation & architecture notes
- Agile methodologies
- Peer mentoring
- Proactive learning, feedback-seeking

# Projects
- **TaskFlow Pro (Kanban Productivity App)**: Personal Angular 17 project. Focus on learning and applying modern Angular: NgRx state, RxJS for UI updates, Angular Material, global theming, robust routing, API integration, and comprehensive documentation. [github.com/alexcarter-dev/taskflow-pro-angular](https://github.com/alexcarter-dev/taskflow-pro-angular)
- **FitTrack Mobile**: React Native app for workout tracking. Local state persistence with AsyncStorage, navigation (React Navigation), styled components, and theme management. [github.com/alexcarter-dev/fittrack-mobile](https://github.com/alexcarter-dev/fittrack-mobile)
- **Campus Event Explorer**: University capstone, co-led development of front-end (React, Node.js, MongoDB). Built routing/navigation and reusable event UIs. Priority on mobile responsiveness and consistency.
- **Student Budget Planner (AngularJS)**: Academic lab app to manage/visualize expenses. Built with client-side routing, controller logic, and mock API.
- **Academic/Practice:** Single-page resume site (HTML, CSS, JS). Responsive photo gallery (CSS Grid). JS utility snippets.

# Awards, Honors, and Recognition
- Promoted from Junior Developer at Northwind Digital Labs within 12 months due to consistently high code quality, clear documentation, and proactive mentorship.

# Languages
- English (fluent)
- No other languages specified

# Activities & Interests
- Attend Portland JavaScript, Angular/Frontend meetups
- Recreate UI patterns from popular apps as practice (CodeSandbox)
- Follow CSS-Tricks, Smashing Magazine, Angular Blog for ongoing learning
- Passionate about UI/UX, accessibility, state management, modern frameworks, and collaborative teams

# Personality Interpretation
_Based on resume content and style (interpretation):_  
Alex likely demonstrates a highly detail-oriented, thoughtful, and communicative approach to work. The resume evidences regular feedback-seeking, proactive initiative, and pride in technical mastery (documentation, test coverage, accessibility). Alex values mentorship (both as a mentee and mentor), process and code quality, and cross-functional teamwork within Agile frameworks. There’s a clear appetite for ongoing learning (tracking new frameworks and best practices) and a collaborative, documentation-driven style suggesting suitability for roles valuing technical rigor and open communication. This interpretation is based on textual clues and may be subjective.

Actively upskilling in modern Angular, NgRx, and RxJS through personal projects, formal online coursework, and deep engagement with the FE community. Academic background in Computer & Information Science with a focus on web development and HCI, and a proven record of both independent and collaborative project delivery. Personality: The resume conveys that Alex Carter is a highly detail-oriented and communication-driven junior front-end developer. Alex consistently emphasizes the importance of thorough documentation, clear commit messages, and PR descriptions, pointing to a conscientious and process-focused work ethic. There is strong evidence of a growth mindset with regular feedback-seeking, active code review participation, and a personal commitment to learning emerging technologies (for example, pursuing advanced Angular knowledge while working mainly in React). Alex seems to value team collaboration, Agile practices, and technical mentoring—both giving and receiving—over purely individual achievement. The writing style is clear, structured, and evidence-focused, highlighting specific metrics (such as improved accessibility scores or testing coverage). There is repeated mention of code maintainability, best practices, and proactive ownership of deliverables, hinting at an intrinsic motivation for quality and continual improvement. This personality interpretation is drawn from resume content and style and should be regarded as a reasoned inference, not a definitive assessment.
